<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1913-12-14T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1913-12-14T00:00:00-05:00" n="568" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d568">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 822.124/322.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">American Minister</gloss> to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Quito</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1913-12-14">
                                    <hi rend="italic">December 14, 1913</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>A contract was signed today in Quito between the Government of Ecuador
                            and James W. McCrosky [sic] representing J. G. White and Company,
                            Limited, of London, for the sanitation works of Guayaquil; the amount
                            involved is about $10,000,000.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Hartman</hi>.</signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                </body></text></TEI>